    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "id": "303d421daa97dc7d",
      "text": "The [[Transmission]] of signals (what is commonly called the transmission performance of communication) is only the means to this end; the function of communication is to enable the summarized reproduction of corresponding (or: approximately corresponding, similar, perhaps only stimulated, but discrepant) [[Selection]] performances elsewhere. Reproducible meaning, then, must first and foremost be communicable. In this respect, language serves not only as a variation mechanism, but also as a selection mechanism of [[Evolution]]."
